Most people think protein = muscle gains. But here’s the truth:
• 🧬 Protein builds every cell — skin, hair, organs, even your immune cells.
• 🧠 It powers your brain — neurotransmitters like serotonin are made from amino acids.
• 🛡️ It fuels your immune system — antibodies? Also proteins.
• 🍽️ It helps you stay full and manage weight.
• 🩹 And it’s critical for healing after injury or surgery.
Bottom line: protein keeps your entire body running — not just your biceps. 💪
👉 Don’t eat protein just for muscles — eat it for your life.

WPL winner with RCB and Indian women's cricketer @shreyanka_patil31 on the first episode of the Blue Rising Vodcast! 

A vodcast where we bring to you some exciting sports persons from the country, their journey, inspiration to take up the sport and much more. 

Watch Shreyanka talk about her journey from winning the WPL with RCB to making it to the Indian Women's cricket team and much more! She talks about success, failure, enjoying the small wins and the way she looks at the sport. 

Join the conversation with Ankit Nagori and learn about the journey of a true champion.

Catch the full episode on the ISH YouTube channel and stay tuned for more athlete stories coming your way! (link in bio)
